<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4272&amp;p=39537#p39537"><![CDATA[
To stop the protection I believe you should search for a JSR $FFA5 which I previously said in this thread contains a INC $0021, RTS. If you search in HEX it would be "20 A5 FF". There should only be one instance of that I would guess. Replace it with "EA EA EA". Then you should be free to modify stuff without tripping the protection. But it's been awhile since I looked at it so I'm just trying to clarify what I said above for you.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Mon Nov 03, 2008 8:25 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
